name: City-owned and Leased Property (Local Law 48 of 2011)

columns.name: Borough
columns.description: The borough that the tax lot is located in.

columns.name: Map Atlas
columns.description: The map on which the property appears in the most recent atlas of the city property

columns.name: Block
columns.description: The tax block that the tax lot is located in.

columns.name: Lot
columns.description: The number of the tax lot.

columns.name: Address
columns.description: An address for the tax lot.

columns.name: Parcel Name
columns.description: General Property name

columns.name: Agency
columns.description: The city agency to which the property is assigned

columns.name: Current Uses
columns.description: Sufficient information to determine the property’s current use or to determine that it has no current use;

columns.name: Total Area
columns.description: Total area, expressed in square feet and rounded to the nearest integer;

columns.name: Open Petroleum Spill
columns.description: Whether the property contains the presence of an open petroleum spill;

columns.name: Govt Clean-Up Program
columns.description: Whether the property is enrolled in a government cleanup, and if so, the name of such program;

top.item: NYC Voluntary Cleanup Program (Not Yet Enrolled)

columns.name: Structure Completed
columns.description: The year construction of the structure(s) was completed and whether such year is an estimate, where applicable;

columns.name: Number Structures
columns.description: The number of structures

columns.name: Total Gross Area Structures
columns.description: Total gross area of all structures expressed in square feet rounded to the nearest integer, where applicable;

columns.name: Ratio Building to Floor Area
columns.description: Ratio of building floor area to the area of the property, where applicable;

columns.name: Allowable Building to Floor Area
columns.description: Allowable ratio of building floor area to the area of the property, where applicable;

columns.name: Land Use Category
columns.description: A code for the tax lot's land use category, modified for display of parks, New York City Department of Parks and Recreation properties and New York State Office of Parks, Recreation and Historic Preservation properties in the appropriate category on land

columns.name: Community Board
columns.description: The community district (CD) or joint interest area (JIA) that the tax lot is located in, or partially located in.

columns.name: Census Tract
columns.description: The 2010 census tract that the tax lot is located in.

columns.name: Census Block
columns.description: The 2010 census block that the tax lot is located in.

columns.name: School Dist
columns.description: The community school district that the tax lot is located in.

columns.name: Council District
columns.description: The city council district that the tax lot is located in.

columns.name: Postcode
columns.description: The zip code that the tax lot is located in.

columns.name: Fire Comp
columns.description: The fire company that services the property;

columns.name: Health Area
columns.description: The health area;

columns.name: Health Ctr
columns.description: The health center district;

columns.name: Police Prct
columns.description: The police precinct;

columns.name: Major Use
columns.description: The major use of the structure or structures, where applicable;

columns.name: Number of Easements
columns.description: The number of easements, where applicable;

columns.name: Commercial Floor Area
columns.description: The exterior dimensions of the portion of the structure or structures allocated for commercial use, where applicable;

columns.name: Residential Floor Area
columns.description: The exterior dimensions of the portion of the structure or structures allocated for residential use, where applicable;

columns.name: Office Floor Area
columns.description: An estimate of the exterior dimensions of the portion of the structure(s) allocated for office use.

columns.name: Retail Floor Area
columns.description: An estimate of the exterior dimensions of the portion of the structure(s) allocated for retail use.

columns.name: Garage Floor Area
columns.description: An estimate of the exterior dimensions of the portion of the structure(s) allocated for garage use.

columns.name: Storage Floor Area
columns.description: An estimate of the exterior dimensions of the portion of the structure(s) allocated for storage or loft purposes.

columns.name: Factory Floor Area
columns.description: An estimate of the exterior dimensions of the portion of the structure(s) allocated for factory, warehouse or loft use.

columns.name: Other Floor Area
columns.description: An estimate of the exterior dimensions of the portion of the structure(s) allocated for other than Residential, Office, Retail, Garage, Storage, Loft or Factory use.

columns.name: Num Floors
columns.description: In the primary building on the tax lot, the number of full and partial stories starting from the ground floor.

columns.name: Residential Units
columns.description: The sum of residential units in all buildings on the tax lot.

columns.name: Residential and Non-Residential Units
columns.description: The sum of residential and non-residential units in all structures, where applicable;

columns.name: Lot Front
columns.description: The frontage, measured in feet;

columns.name: Lot Depth
columns.description: The depth, measured in feet;

columns.name: Bldg Front
columns.description: The frontage along the street, measured in feet;

columns.name: Bldg Depth
columns.description: The depth of the structure or structures, which is the effective perpendicular distance, measured in feet, where applicable;

columns.name: Proximity Code
columns.description: Whether the structure or structures are detached, semi-detached or attached to neighboring structures, where applicable;

columns.name: Irr Lot Code
columns.description: Whether the property is irregularly shaped;

columns.name: Lot Type Code
columns.description: The location relative to another lot or water, expressed as mixed or unknown, block assemblage, waterfront, corner, through, inside, interior, island, alley, or submerged land;

columns.name: Bsmt Code
columns.description: A code describing the basement.

columns.name: Assess Land
columns.description: The actual assessed land value for Fiscal Year 2013.

columns.name: Exempt Land
columns.description: The actual exempt land value, which is determined differently for each exemption program, is the dollar amount related to that portion of the tax lot that has received an exemption or abatement for Fiscal Year 2013.

columns.name: Exempt Tot
columns.description: The actual exempt total value, which is determined differently for each exemption program, is the dollar amount related to that portion of the tax lot that has received an exemption or abatement for Fiscal Year 2013.

columns.name: Year Alter 1
columns.description: If a building has only been altered once, this is the date of the alteration.

columns.name: Year Alter 2
columns.description: If a building has been altered more than once, this is the year of the most recent alteration.

columns.name: His Dist
columns.description: The name of the Historic District as designated by the New York City Landmarks Preservation Commission.

top.item: Crown Heights North III Historic Distric

columns.name: Landmark
columns.description: The name of an individual landmark, landmark site (e.g. Richmondtown Restoration), or an interior landmark, as designated by the New York City Landmarks Preservation Commission.

columns.name: Condominium Number
columns.description: The condominium number assigned to the complex, where applicable;

columns.name: Coordinates
columns.description: The coordinate of the XY coordinate pair that depicts the property’s approximate location as expressed in the New York-Long Island State Plane coordination system;

columns.name: E-Designation Number
columns.description: The e-designation number associated with the property, where applicable;

columns.name: Industrial Business Zone
columns.description: Whether the property is located in an industrial business zone;

columns.name: Zone Dist 1
columns.description: The primary zoning classification of the property;

columns.name: Zone Dist 2
columns.description: The zoning designation occupying the second greatest percentage of the property’s area, where applicable;

columns.name: Overlay 1
columns.description: The primary commercial overlay assigned to the property, where applicable;

columns.name: Overlay 2
columns.description: The commercial overlay occupying the second greatest percentage of the property’s area, where applicable;

columns.name: SP Dist 1
columns.description: The special purpose district assigned to the tax lot.

columns.name: SP Dist 2
columns.description: The special purpose district assigned to the tax lot.

columns.name: Potential Urban Ag
columns.description: Whether the land is suitable for urban agriculture (for description, click “About” then “Attachments”)

columns.name: Contact
columns.description: Agency contact information, including name, telephone number and email address.

columns.description: For each property assigned to the economic development corporation, such list shall include the percentage of usable space actually occupied by a tenant or tenants.
